 Aerial photo taken on Nov. 26, 2021 shows a view of the expansion project of Meilan International Airport in Haikou, south China's Hainan Province. The expansion project of Meilan International Airport in south China's resort island of Hainan was officially put into operation on Dec. 2. The project consists of a new terminal, a 3,600-meter runway, and ground transport facilities. (Xinhua/Yang Guanyu)  Aerial photo taken on Nov. 26, 2021 shows a view of the expansion project of Meilan International Airport in Haikou, south China's Hainan Province. The expansion project of Meilan International Airport in south China's resort island of Hainan was officially put into operation on Dec. 2. The project consists of a new terminal, a 3,600-meter runway, and ground transport facilities. (Xinhua/Yang Guanyu)  Passengers check in at Terminal 2 of Meilan International Airport in Haikou, south China's Hainan Province, Dec. 2, 2021. The expansion project of Meilan International Airport in south China's resort island of Hainan was officially put into operation on Dec. 2. The project consists of a new terminal, a 3,600-meter runway, and ground transport facilities. (Xinhua/Yang Guanyu)  A passenger takes photos of the boarding pass at Terminal 2 of Meilan International Airport in Haikou, south China's Hainan Province, Dec. 2, 2021. The expansion project of Meilan International Airport in south China's resort island of Hainan was officially put into operation on Dec. 2. The project consists of a new terminal, a 3,600-meter runway, and ground transport facilities. (Xinhua/Yang Guanyu)  Aerial photo taken on Nov. 26, 2021 shows a view of the expansion project of Meilan International Airport in Haikou, south China's Hainan Province. The expansion project of Meilan International Airport in south China's resort island of Hainan was officially put into operation on Dec. 2. The project consists of a new terminal, a 3,600-meter runway, and ground transport facilities. (Xinhua/Yang Guanyu)